(c) Write a Methods section for the protocol used in the style of the journal Microbial Genomics (Up to 300 words, 20%).

**Methods**

To analyse the metagenomic sequences, we employed a four-step process involving quality control, read trimming, de novo assembly, and assembly assessment, as outlined below. The analysis was performed using the following raw sequence data: coursework2023_R1.fastq and coursework2023_R2.fastq.

Quality control: `FastQC` was used to assess the quality of the raw sequence data by generating summary statistics and visualizing the distribution of base quality scores. This step ensured the suitability of the dataset for downstream analysis.

Trimming: `Trimmomatic` was employed to remove low-quality bases and adapter sequences. The command line used for this purpose was as follows:

```bash
java -jar ./tools/Trimmomatic-0.39/trimmomatic-0.39.jar PE coursework2023_R1.fastq coursework2023_R2.fastq out_R1_paired.fastq out_R1_unpaired.fastq out_R2_paired.fastq out_R2_unpaired.fastq LEADING:20 TRAILING:20 SLIDINGWINDOW:4:15 MINLEN:50
```

The parameters used were: LEADING and TRAILING set to remove score below 20; SLIDINGWINDOW with a window size of 4 bp and a threshold of 15 to ensure an average base quality score >15 within the sliding window; MINLEN set to 50 to discard reads shorter than 50 bp after trimming. If without MINLEN, there will be some reads just 1bp:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

This step generated two paired-end output files: **out_R1_paired.fastq** and **out_R2_paired.fastq**.

De novo assembly: MEGAHIT was utilized to assemble the high-quality paired-end reads into contigs. The following command was executed and will generate a FASTA named  `final.contigs.fa`:
```bash
/megahit -1 out_R1_paired.fastq -2 out_R2_paired.fastq -o final.contigs.fa
```

Assembly assessment: QUAST was used to evaluate the quality and accuracy of the assembled contigs.
```bash
quast assembly_all_contigs/final.contigs.fa
```

QUAST generated an report including metrics such as the number of contigs, N50, L50, total length. This allowed for the evaluation of the assembly quality and facilitated further analysis and interpretation of the metagenomic data.
